Jannik Sinner and Daniil Medvedev will meet in the BNP Paribas Open final on Sunday in Indian Wells, California.

Sunday's champion will also depart Indian Wells with a hefty payday. The winner will claim $1,151,380, while the runner-up will earn $612,340. Look below for a full prize-money breakdown of the singles field at the season's first ATP Masters 1000 event.



















































































